ownedNfts.name: The community
ownedNfts.description:
"The Community" is inspired by helping each other in the NFT community. Sometimes you may have heard that the cryptocurrency world is full of scams.  
But since I have been working full time artist with this community. I met great new friends and gained much support from this community. We communicate with our artistic tastes. We give advice and encourage each other like they give a special gift.  
I want to include the stories of happiness in this community in every piece of my artwork.

Merry Christmas.

ownedNfts.name: Heavy Metal: The Wizard of the North
ownedNfts.description: Unnamed, unknown and magically proficient, the wizard of the north is left to his own devices. A relic of an ancient time, the people of Syrinthia know not to disturb the balance of power and interfere with magics unknown to them. However an evil is brewing in the East, an unseen magic from times before man has awoken. Leaving only 1 question to be had - Do the people of Syrinthia request an audience of the Wizard pleading him for his protection against this forign enemy, or do they leave him forsaken, too scared of the Wizard Of The North to plead for his help as they face a new enemy in which they have no hopes of conquering without him. First appearance: Heavy Metal cover, issue #306

Tiles are a celebration of what gives meaning to those communities: the individual.There is one Tile generated for every possible ETH wallet addresseach representing a unique identity in the decentralized ecosystem that makes projects like this possible.Mathematically, all Tiles are equally rare. They are all fashioned from the same assortment of simple shapes and colors, but each in a unique way. In that sense, Tiles are a bit like us.Owning a Tile is an invitation to participate in the TileDAO, which receives all revenue from the Tiles primary sale. Because the supply is virtually infinite, funding for the DAO may continue indefinitelyas long as Tiles are sold. - peri.eth

Because the supply is virtually infinite, funding for the DAO may continue indefinitely, as long as Tiles are sold. - peri.eth

ownedNfts.name: Reasons #14
ownedNfts.description:
I wrote and produced Reasons as a just a fun song about why I be low key to be honest. A lot of time in the entertainment industry, ppl equate your fame level with your quality of life. But most of the ppl I look up to who have what I consider to be a high quality of life arent necessarily famous. Ive found when you keep your wins & happiness private it tends to last longer. 

Basically all forces of power Ive been involved in from management to labels are motivated to keep you ignorant enough about business, but worth it just enough so you keep creating for them. Its a lot easier and faster to make the most $ off someone's back the more ignorant they are in the traditional industry. Id say Ive gotten got in every way possible, from bad deals, stolen ideas, not paid after a sold out tour, etc. But all of that taught me so much about business. I took some of my $ invested in real estate and did some good flips w/ my manager Jay, bought myself outta bad deals and learned how to fund my lifestyle and career completely outside of the traditional industry. Through real estate development and investing, Im also able to give and hire POC through my businesses and my non profit "Yebo Life". 

The meme coins and Wall Street Bets stocks dont hurt either. In our label, Mogul Sound Music, we want our artists to be as knowledgeable as possible about business and investing because it helps all of us get sharper. The more our artists know, the more they succeed, and the more responsibility they put on themselves to be great.
